      • getMapInfo

        public java.lang.Object getMapInfo()
        Description copied from interface: UniqueMapInterface
        Get the name of the stored Map. It is always possible that one Map file or source is "opened" more than once with different unique IDs. The name may be a simple name, or it may be the name of a file, a fullpath to a file, or some other Object as needed by the implementation.
        Specified by:
